description:
A Solar Sales Representative needs to demonstrate the long-term financial value of premium Lithium Iron Phosphate (LFP) batteries over cheaper Lead-Acid (AGM) alternatives to a homeowner in Phoenix, Arizona. Create a residential PV plus battery storage project (5.0 kW DC PV, 10.0 kWh battery capacity, 5.0 kW power rating) using a bundled TMY weather file for Phoenix, AZ. Compare the 25-year Net Present Value (NPV) and the Present Value of Battery Replacement Costs between Scenario A (Lead-Acid AGM) and Scenario B (Lithium-Ion LFP). For both scenarios, configure the system to replace the battery at an 80% capacity threshold with a replacement cost of $300 per kWh.

Extract the results and save them to /home/ga/Documents/SAM_Projects/battery_chemistry_comparison.json using this structure:
{
  "system_size_kw": 5.0,
  "battery_capacity_kwh": 10.0,
  "scenarios": {
    "lead_acid": {
      "npv_dollars": <value>,
      "pv_battery_replacement_cost_dollars": <value>
    },
    "lithium_ion_lfp": {
      "npv_dollars": <value>,
      "pv_battery_replacement_cost_dollars": <value>
    }
  }
}

Save the SAM project file to /home/ga/Documents/SAM_Projects/battery_comparison.sam or the PySAM script to /home/ga/Documents/SAM_Projects/compare_batteries.py.
